knots, and the pillow a sort of frightful hot, as though a baked brick had been 
on it? A hot old man! I guess he’s got what some folks ashore call a 
conscience; it’s a kind of Tic-Dolly-row they say—worse nor a toothache. 
Well, well; I don’t know what it is, but the Lord keep me from catching it. 
He’s full of riddles; I wonder what he goes into the after hold for, every 
